By the way, if it is the *true* BSD licence (ie the code is copyright 
Berkeley University :-) then the BSD and the MIT stuff are equivalent.

Berkeley has, to the best of my knowledge, deleted clause 3 from all the 
software to which they own the copyright. (Precisely because it was 
incompatible with the GPL, I believe...)

